Description: Colour pale red. Integumental papillae short, slightly curved (
Fig. 12 l – n
). Lateral eye lens diameter anterior 40 – 70, posterior 30 – 60, separation 50 – 150. Medial margin of Cx-I with distinct projections associated with setal bases; tips Cx-I with very few (2 – 4) strong setae, a few further strong setae posterolaterally on Cx-I, and antero- and posterolaterally on Cx-II and –III ( Figs 12 k , 13 a ). Medial margin of Cx-I with 5 – 9, posterior margin of Cx-IV with 10 – 21 setae in a single, slightly irregular row. Posterolateral apodeme of Cx-IV long, oblique to the median axis ( Fig. 13 a ). Swimming setae (anterior/posterior) II-L-5, 0/1 – 2; III-L-4, 0/5 – 15; III-L-5, 0/5 – 12; IV-L-4, 7 – 14/7 – 14; IV-L-5, 0/5 – 10. Leg claw length (all legs) 23 – 35; L ratio claw/ I-IV-L-5, 6 – 13 %. Leg segments slender (e.g., L/H ratio I-L-5, 4.8 – 6.5; II-L-5, 6.4 – 7.7; III-L-5, 5.6 – 7.3; IV-L-5, 7.0 – 8.4–see
Fig. 13 b – c
).
